[normal]Background [bold]to Scape[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Scape has been procuring on behalf of the public sector
[normal] for over 10 years
[normal].  It is a Local Authority owned and controlled company that specialises in construction as this is the biggest procurement category of spend in Local Government (Roots Review, 2009).  Scape’s 
[normal]procurement arrangements
[normal] have grown to 8 contracts
[normal] total
[normal]ling £4
[normal]bn in 
[normal]project value.  300
[normal] 
[normal]public sector clients use Scape delivering over 1200
[normal] 
[normal]projects. All procurement arrangements
[normal] are 100% market tested, 100% cla
[normal]im free, delivered savings of £200
[normal]M and offer the most efficient route to market in the UK
[normal] for LA’s.  Example of our services is shown below:
[normal]In March 2013 the LGA published LG Procurement: Rising to the Challenge and Scape sits on the NPS construction steering group, working with local and central government colleagues to help delivery efficiencies in procurement. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In July 2013 the Government published the Construction 2025 - Industrial Strategy. Scape are already delivering the savings identified in the strategy and are pro-actively working with Government to support the rest of the industry to achieve similar efficiencies. 
[normal]&#xa0;
